  "texts": [
    "This step-wise reasoning is equally applicable to refining test oracles.",
    "TestChain [84] achieves this by creating a calculator agent that interacts with a Python interpreter within a ReAct (Reason-Act) loop.",
    "It decomposes the calculation of expected outputs into sequential steps, executing code snippets and observing results to derive correct assertion values, thereby effectively mitigating assertion errors caused by the computational limitations of LLMs.",
    "A large-scale evaluation of various prompting strategies [103] systematically compared CoT and Tree of Thoughts (ToT), among others, confirming their significant advantages in improving test logic and comprehensiveness.",
    "The concept of task decomposition has also been extended to educational contexts."
  ],
